definitions.definition: Someone who terminates or ends something, especially (in later use) an assassin or exterminator .
A text character or string that serves to mark the end of a document or transmission.
The line between the day side and the night side of a moon , planet or other celestial body.
A DNA sequence that causes RNA transcription to cease and an mRNA transcript to break off.
An electrical device that absorbs reflection at the end of a transmission line .
An intelligent android created to destroy humans.

main_definition: Someone who terminates or ends something, especially (in later use) an assassin or exterminator . [from 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( computing ) A text character or string that serves to mark the end of a document or transmission.
( astronomy ) The line between the day side and the night side of a moon , planet or other celestial body. [from 17th c.]
( biochemistry ) A DNA sequence that causes RNA transcription to cease and an mRNA transcript to break off. [from 20th c.]
( electronics ) An electrical device that absorbs reflection at the end of a transmission line .
( science fiction ) An intelligent android created to destroy humans.
